<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 29 at 1:47AM CDT  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of northwestern Washita,
northern Greer and eastern Beckham Counties through 215 AM CDT...
At 147 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Elk City to 5 miles south of Carter to 8
miles southwest of Willow. Movement was east at 5 mph. Other strong
thunderstorms were located near Sayre and near Delhi.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Elk City, Sayre, Canute, Carter, Willow, Retrop, Delhi and Brinkman.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
